The paper deals with semi-supervised learning on 3D data, specifically volumetric data in medical imaging. The proposed method involves generating different views of the data by rotating it, and utilizing asymmetrical 3D kernels to encourage diversified features. The paper also proposes an uncertainty-aware attention mechanism to estimate the reliability of each view prediction with Bayesian deep learning. Given these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and multimedia (cs.MM).
